From: mhtrinh <notifications@github.com>
Sent: Wednesday, October 10, 2018 22:09
To: tensorflow/tensorflow
Cc: stillwalker1234; Comment
Subject: Re: [tensorflow/tensorflow] DataLossError (see above for traceback): corrupted record at 12 (#13463)


I am not sure this is acceptable behavior : we are lucky that the CRC check failed, otherwise you will be silently training with corrupted data which is kind of scary. Some may say this is a kind data augmentation? ;-)

I am not sure this is acceptable behavior : we are lucky that the CRC check failed, otherwise you will be silently training with corrupted data which is kind of scary. Some may say this is a kind data augmentation? ;-)
